WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.001 --> 00:00:02.461
<i>Previously on</i> Will Trent...

2
00:00:02.544 --> 00:00:04.296
<i>Adelaide knows where my uncle is.</i>

3
00:00:04.379 --> 00:00:05.631
Adelaide!

4
00:00:05.714 --> 00:00:08.008
<i>I'm sorry. bud. She's gone.</i>

5
00:00:08.550 --> 00:00:11.720
Antonio could be dead or worse.
Nobody has any answers.

6
00:00:11.803 --> 00:00:16.141
The best way to get to Antonio
has to be Jeb Oswald.

7
00:00:16.225 --> 00:00:18.685
What is Adelaide doing?

8
00:00:18.769 --> 00:00:21.980
I get my instructions from somebody else.
His name is The Commander.

9
00:00:22.064 --> 00:00:24.775
- Adelaide must really trust you.
- We understand each other.

10
00:00:25.692 --> 00:00:26.944
- What's this?
- We'll be in touch.

11
00:00:27.027 --> 00:00:29.196
<i>You have no sightings of Adelaide Trevens?</i>

12
00:00:29.279 --> 00:00:31.782
No. it has not rung yet.

13
00:00:31.865 --> 00:00:33.700
<i>He's my family. Ange.</i>

14
00:00:33.784 --> 00:00:34.785
They're gonna find him.

15
00:00:42.709 --> 00:00:45.295
Help! Help me.

16
00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:53.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

17
00:01:24.626 --> 00:01:25.627
No drugs.

18
00:01:28.547 --> 00:01:32.384
Just a student ID and a library card.

19
00:01:32.467 --> 00:01:36.430
We've got stolen mail.
fraudulent loan applications.

20
00:01:36.513 --> 00:01:39.141
Sweet Dylan Rome. What are you doing here?

21
00:01:40.976 --> 00:01:43.645
Well. this room's a DNA nightmare.

22
00:01:46.732 --> 00:01:48.567
- Let's get these bagged.
- All right.

23
00:01:51.361 --> 00:01:52.446
Let's follow this blood trail.

24
00:02:07.794 --> 00:02:09.129
Two more casings right here.

25
00:02:12.090 --> 00:02:13.800
9-mil. same caliber.

26
00:02:15.302 --> 00:02:17.179
Hey. let's make sure
we get these bagged up too.

27
00:02:17.262 --> 00:02:18.472
Yeah. there's a trail.

28
00:02:23.852 --> 00:02:25.228
Shooter had to come this way.

29
00:02:25.312 --> 00:02:28.065
The evidence techs are gonna
have a blast bagging up all this trash.

30
00:02:29.024 --> 00:02:30.692
That bench has
your name all over it. Franklin.

31
00:02:30.776 --> 00:02:32.152
No. looks better in your house.

32
00:02:36.990 --> 00:02:38.867
Ah. jackpot.

33
00:02:40.285 --> 00:02:42.496
Brand-new video game system
out here all by itself.

34
00:02:42.579 --> 00:02:44.122
You think that's Dylan's blood on it?

35
00:02:44.206 --> 00:02:46.875
I mean. no.
Otherwise. how did he end up inside?

36
00:02:46.958 --> 00:02:49.711
Maybe Dylan was shooting at someone trying
to steal a video game system.

37
00:02:50.379 --> 00:02:51.546
That kid is not a killer.

38
00:02:52.631 --> 00:02:54.216
Maybe we found our second victim.

39
00:02:54.299 --> 00:02:55.592
Could still be alive.

40
00:02:56.551 --> 00:02:59.471
- Hey. let's bag this.
- You got it.

41
00:03:00.305 --> 00:03:03.058
- Huh.
- No one here is gonna tell us anything.

42
00:03:03.141 --> 00:03:04.309
Well. there is that guy.

43
00:03:06.770 --> 00:03:08.063
Can't hurt to try.

44
00:03:09.606 --> 00:03:10.982
It absolutely can.

45
00:03:14.319 --> 00:03:15.404
Excuse me. sir.

46
00:03:15.904 --> 00:03:18.073
The shooting. you see what happened?

47
00:03:18.573 --> 00:03:19.950
No. sir. I'm blind.

48
00:03:20.701 --> 00:03:23.120
Great. Let's pull
whatever camera footage we can find.

49
00:03:23.203 --> 00:03:25.080
Hold up. we got a witness right here.

50
00:03:25.580 --> 00:03:27.582
The witness didn't see anything. literally.

51
00:03:27.666 --> 00:03:28.750
Yeah. but he's blind.

52
00:03:28.834 --> 00:03:30.585
That's exactly what I just said.

53
00:03:30.669 --> 00:03:31.962
Haven't you heard of Daredevil?

54
00:03:32.546 --> 00:03:33.880
Maybe his senses got sharper.

55
00:03:33.964 --> 00:03:35.632
The man got ears. a nose.

56
00:03:35.715 --> 00:03:38.552
Kid you're looking for ran for his life.
got shot.

57
00:03:38.635 --> 00:03:41.430
Some Good Samaritan scooped him up.

58
00:03:44.850 --> 00:03:46.726
Did you happen to see...

59
00:03:48.270 --> 00:03:50.355
- Any idea who pulled the trigger?
- Not here.

60
00:03:51.731 --> 00:03:54.860
- Maybe you buy Mac a sandwich first?
- Yeah. okay. Franklin?

61
00:03:54.943 --> 00:03:56.987
I'ma start calling hospitals.
You take his order.

62
00:04:01.658 --> 00:04:03.285
What do you want. like. a ham and cheese?

63
00:04:03.869 --> 00:04:05.203
Not if you want me to talk.

64
00:04:05.745 --> 00:04:08.582
That's ridiculous.
How can they say there's no metadata?

65
00:04:08.665 --> 00:04:10.083
There's always metadata.

66
00:04:10.167 --> 00:04:12.669
<i>That's the whole point of metadata.</i>

67
00:04:12.752 --> 00:04:14.045
<i>They're the FBI.</i>

68
00:04:14.129 --> 00:04:16.548
Oh. you think
I'm holding out on you. huh?

69
00:04:16.631 --> 00:04:20.343
Caroline. is there any new intel
on Adelaide Trevens

70
00:04:20.427 --> 00:04:22.262
that we have not forwarded
to Special Agent Trent?

71
00:04:22.345 --> 00:04:25.557
No. ma'am. you gave me clear instructions
to share everything.

72
00:04:25.640 --> 00:04:28.810
- I've kept a spreadsheet.
- I appreciate it. Caroline. Thank you.

73
00:04:28.894 --> 00:04:30.479
<i>You just mad she's making you wait.</i>

74
00:04:30.562 --> 00:04:33.982
I mean. why give me a phone
if she's not going to use it?

75
00:04:34.065 --> 00:04:36.526
He's alive. Will.
You and I both know that.

76
00:04:39.029 --> 00:04:40.989
- Printed copy of your speech.
- Oh. thanks.

77
00:04:41.072 --> 00:04:42.240
- Speech?
<i>- Oh!</i>

78
00:04:42.365 --> 00:04:43.658
<i>Deputy Director Wagner...</i>

79
00:04:43.742 --> 00:04:45.202
<i>is giving a speech
at a leadership conference</i>

80
00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:47.287
<i>with some very important people.</i>

81
00:04:47.370 --> 00:04:50.916
It's just a hotel ballroom.
Sad lettuce and weak coffee.

82
00:04:50.999 --> 00:04:53.293
With some very impressive people.

83
00:04:53.376 --> 00:04:55.086
<i>Well. I'm very impressed.</i>

84
00:04:55.170 --> 00:04:57.005
<i>I keep telling you. you should be.</i>

85
00:04:57.088 --> 00:04:58.590
Okay. I'm going.

86
00:04:58.673 --> 00:05:01.802
If that Adelaide phone rings.
I am leaving wherever I am.

87
00:05:01.885 --> 00:05:02.969
no matter who's there.

88
00:05:03.053 --> 00:05:05.514
- You understand?
- Yeah. who else am I gonna call?

89
00:05:05.597 --> 00:05:06.681
I keep telling you.

90
00:05:24.991 --> 00:05:26.618
I ruined the potatoes.

91
00:05:28.495 --> 00:05:29.496
Nico.

92
00:05:30.747 --> 00:05:32.749
What happened? Let me see.

93
00:05:32.833 --> 00:05:34.793
- It's not that bad.
- It is that bad.

94
00:05:34.876 --> 00:05:36.628
I see bone. Keep it elevated.

95
00:05:36.711 --> 00:05:38.880
No. that's potato.

96
00:05:38.964 --> 00:05:40.799
No. it's not. Okay?
You got to keep it elevated.

97
00:05:40.882 --> 00:05:43.218
- We're going to the ER.
- Tell Betty I love her.

98
00:05:44.052 --> 00:05:45.971
Okay. Come on. Nico.

99
00:05:48.807 --> 00:05:50.100
She has hair.

100
00:05:51.434 --> 00:05:53.520
I hope she's a redhead.

101
00:05:54.271 --> 00:05:56.565
There's hair inside my uterus.

102
00:05:57.691 --> 00:05:59.442
- It's gross.
- Absolutely.

103
00:05:59.526 --> 00:06:01.194
- Right?
- Yeah. But also amazing.

104
00:06:01.278 --> 00:06:02.821
- I mean. right?
- I mean. yeah. It is. I mean...

105
00:06:02.904 --> 00:06:05.532
If you think that's gross. just wait.

106
00:06:08.451 --> 00:06:11.913
Try to enjoy this time.
It's the calm before the storm.

107
00:06:12.706 --> 00:06:14.207
Thank you. Dr. Gundis. We will.

108
00:06:16.167 --> 00:06:17.168
Sorry.

109
00:06:17.252 --> 00:06:18.879
Hey. they made it almost the full hour.

110
00:06:18.962 --> 00:06:20.213
Almost.

111
00:06:20.297 --> 00:06:21.798
"Bus accident." We got to go.

112
00:06:21.882 --> 00:06:24.509
So from here on out.
I want to see you every week. okay?

113
00:06:24.593 --> 00:06:27.804
Just to make sure your sweet little angel
is happy and healthy.

114
00:06:27.888 --> 00:06:29.306
And it's time for desk duty.

115
00:06:29.931 --> 00:06:32.851
So soon. I thought you could
make it another month or two.

116
00:06:32.934 --> 00:06:34.561
you know. maybe through labor...

117
00:06:34.644 --> 00:06:36.897
- It's fine. I'm ready. I can do it.
- Okay.

118
00:06:49.326 --> 00:06:52.412
- Excuse me. I need Dr. Chambliss.
- I'll see if I can find him.

119
00:06:52.495 --> 00:06:54.789
Tell him it's about Kevin's eyes.
It's urgent.

120
00:06:55.749 --> 00:06:58.418
<i>I don't know who this
is worse for. you or Nico.</i>

121
00:06:58.501 --> 00:07:00.545
Woman. it was an emergency. okay?

122
00:07:00.629 --> 00:07:03.590
And in case you forgot. I can't read.

123
00:07:03.673 --> 00:07:06.593
so I went to the one place
I know how to get to. Just...

124
00:07:06.676 --> 00:07:09.137
Big mistake. You'll just get sick
sitting in the waiting room.

125
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:12.390
and you'll end up in urgent care. where
you should've went in the first place.

126
00:07:12.474 --> 00:07:13.767
Yeah. whatever.

127
00:07:14.476 --> 00:07:16.102
Here. I got you.

128
00:07:17.270 --> 00:07:19.314
It's... What?

129
00:07:19.397 --> 00:07:22.484
<i>Who's helping you? I bet it's not
anyone with medical training.</i>

130
00:07:24.235 --> 00:07:25.695
Okay. Much obliged.

131
00:07:25.779 --> 00:07:27.572
Down with King George.

132
00:07:27.656 --> 00:07:30.909
Okay. Um. I'll call you
when I get out of here.

133
00:07:30.992 --> 00:07:32.702
I'll talk to you in 20 years.

134
00:07:32.786 --> 00:07:33.870
Ha ha.

135
00:07:43.755 --> 00:07:46.424
- It's a madhouse today. huh?
- Just another Tuesday.

136
00:07:47.092 --> 00:07:48.259
Hmm.

137
00:07:49.719 --> 00:07:51.012
You have to hold it.

138
00:07:51.096 --> 00:07:53.682
- I know. but you've gotta hold it.
- What are you doing here?

139
00:07:53.765 --> 00:07:55.684
Hey. Seth and I had baby stuff upstairs.

140
00:07:55.767 --> 00:07:57.894
- Wait. No.
- Hey.

141
00:08:00.063 --> 00:08:01.356
Give it.

142
00:08:01.439 --> 00:08:04.567
Hey. how did you let this happen?
I told you to get rid of that mandoline.

143
00:08:04.651 --> 00:08:07.028
A mandoline is an excellent tool
when used safely.

144
00:08:07.654 --> 00:08:09.614
Are you blaming the victim?

145
00:08:10.281 --> 00:08:11.825
And why is it called a mandoline?

146
00:08:11.908 --> 00:08:13.243
Oh. you prefer "they-them-doline"?

147
00:08:13.326 --> 00:08:14.744
How about a "cut-your-hand-oline"?

148
00:08:16.413 --> 00:08:18.957
Dr. Chambliss?
I need to talk to Dr. Chambliss.

149
00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:21.584
- Please stay in the room...
- Why isn't anybody listening to me?

150
00:08:21.668 --> 00:08:24.170
I need to speak to Dr. Chambliss.
There's something wrong with my son...

151
00:08:24.254 --> 00:08:25.922
He is making his rounds right now.

152
00:08:26.548 --> 00:08:29.968
Dr. Chambliss.
Kevin's eyes are still moving.

153
00:08:30.051 --> 00:08:31.761
You told me that they would stop.

154
00:08:31.845 --> 00:08:34.556
Something is wrong.
I'm telling you. it's a seizure.

155
00:08:34.639 --> 00:08:36.558
Your son is fine. He's stable.

156
00:08:37.058 --> 00:08:38.351
It's normal for his eyes to move.

157
00:08:38.435 --> 00:08:41.438
As I've explained. he's been sedated
so the bullet in his neck stays put

158
00:08:41.521 --> 00:08:42.897
until we can move him to surgery.

159
00:08:42.981 --> 00:08:46.192
As I explained. he gets seizures.

160
00:08:46.276 --> 00:08:49.112
I know people like you don't like
to listen to people like me.

161
00:08:49.195 --> 00:08:51.823
but if you don't.
he's gonna get brain damage.

162
00:08:51.906 --> 00:08:53.950
I'm his mother.
I know that there is something wrong.

163
00:08:54.034 --> 00:08:56.244
I'm his doctor. I'll take a look at him
when I have a chance.

164
00:08:56.327 --> 00:08:58.955
- Hey. don't you walk away from me.
- Look. you can leave.

165
00:09:00.832 --> 00:09:03.126
Or you can explain to social services
why your pupils are dilated.

166
00:09:03.209 --> 00:09:05.378
- Why won't you listen to me?
- How about we get some air?

167
00:09:05.462 --> 00:09:08.590
Get your hands off of me! You are cooking
his brain. You're gonna let him die.

168
00:09:08.673 --> 00:09:11.676
He is stable. we are helping him.
You don't know what you're talking about.

169
00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:14.512
Excuse me.
I'm Special Agent Will Trent with the GBI.

170
00:09:14.596 --> 00:09:16.014
Great. Get her out of here.

171
00:09:16.097 --> 00:09:17.557
"Get her out of here"?

172
00:09:18.141 --> 00:09:19.934
Whoa!

173
00:09:20.018 --> 00:09:21.770
Down. get down.

174
00:09:22.854 --> 00:09:25.857
Nobody leaves until my son gets help.

175
00:09:29.110 --> 00:09:32.614
{\an8}Mmm...

176
00:09:34.783 --> 00:09:35.867
{\an8}Great sandwich.

177
00:09:37.118 --> 00:09:39.788
{\an8}You know. most places don't
soak the bread crumbs. so...

178
00:09:40.747 --> 00:09:41.998
{\an8}then the meatballs get tough.

179
00:09:42.082 --> 00:09:44.250
{\an8}You know. Mac.
you kind of agreed to tell us

180
00:09:44.334 --> 00:09:46.294
{\an8}what you know
when we bought you that sandwich.

181
00:09:52.717 --> 00:09:55.136
{\an8}I can't do this.

182
00:09:58.807 --> 00:10:00.100
{\an8}Any time. man.

183
00:10:00.183 --> 00:10:01.434
{\an8}Just before Jesus comes back.

184
00:10:04.562 --> 00:10:07.273
{\an8}Osiris. Real scary dude.

185
00:10:08.900 --> 00:10:10.610
{\an8}He took over the block about a month ago.

186
00:10:10.693 --> 00:10:12.445
{\an8}and since then it's been hot.

187
00:10:12.529 --> 00:10:15.532
{\an8}Hot like the equator in August.
you understand?

188
00:10:16.157 --> 00:10:19.369
{\an8}You see. anybody can
plant their flag in the mud.

189
00:10:20.161 --> 00:10:22.914
{\an8}But it takes time for that flag
to stand on its own.

190
00:10:23.873 --> 00:10:25.500
{\an8}The mud needs to dry. you feel me?

191
00:10:25.583 --> 00:10:28.711
{\an8}So Osiris is trying to prove
to everyone in town he's not a punk.

192
00:10:29.379 --> 00:10:30.839
{\an8}As a result. he's been extra violent.

193
00:10:30.922 --> 00:10:33.675
{\an8}Arm for a hand. a head for an eye.

194
00:10:34.175 --> 00:10:36.594
{\an8}Forget precedent.
This is "prece-don't-try."

195
00:10:37.720 --> 00:10:40.640
{\an8}But that's what it takes. you understand?

196
00:10:40.723 --> 00:10:42.058
{\an8}Yeah. we understand.

197
00:10:42.142 --> 00:10:43.143
{\an8}Amen.

198
00:10:46.521 --> 00:10:49.315
{\an8}A-Amen.

199
00:10:51.484 --> 00:10:53.069
{\an8}- Amen.
- Amen.

200
00:10:55.071 --> 00:10:59.200
{\an8}So as I was saying. I hear those two boys
going to that trap house.

201
00:10:59.284 --> 00:11:01.369
{\an8}Couldn't have been long
before I started hearing gunshots.

202
00:11:01.452 --> 00:11:04.289
{\an8}One of them come running out yelling.
"Help me. help!"

203
00:11:05.373 --> 00:11:08.459
{\an8}Innocent as a dove. before "bang. bang!"

204
00:11:10.044 --> 00:11:11.546
{\an8}Thoughts and prayers. you understand?

205
00:11:13.131 --> 00:11:14.924
{\an8}- Y'all got any more ice?
- No.

206
00:11:16.009 --> 00:11:17.635
Now. do you think those kids was trying

207
00:11:17.719 --> 00:11:19.804
to steal the video game system
from Osiris?

208
00:11:19.888 --> 00:11:21.806
If they were. they learned their lesson.

209
00:11:21.890 --> 00:11:24.559
And you can bet Osiris left it there

210
00:11:24.642 --> 00:11:27.103
so everybody else can learn theirs too.

211
00:11:27.187 --> 00:11:29.731
- It's a flag in the mud.
- Mm-hmm.

212
00:11:29.814 --> 00:11:31.691
Y'all better find that boy who got away.

213
00:11:32.525 --> 00:11:34.402
If he ain't dead yet. he will be soon.

214
00:11:36.446 --> 00:11:38.114
Can y'all take me to get some cigarettes?

215
00:11:38.865 --> 00:11:40.617
- It's right up the street.
- Oh. absolutely not.

216
00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:42.577
- If y'all don't mind.
- No. no. we mind.

217
00:11:51.586 --> 00:11:53.755
Let me know if there's anything else
you want me to do.

218
00:12:01.012 --> 00:12:02.013
Hey. you okay?

219
00:12:03.973 --> 00:12:05.850
I don't know. Are we?

220
00:12:06.559 --> 00:12:09.062
Yeah. as long as we stay calm.

221
00:12:14.400 --> 00:12:15.944
Hey. Hey.

222
00:12:17.654 --> 00:12:18.988
Just take deep breaths.

223
00:12:24.577 --> 00:12:26.913
- You help him!
- Okay. I'm gonna check your son's chart.

224
00:12:26.996 --> 00:12:28.623
but first. tell me what I should know.

225
00:12:28.706 --> 00:12:31.960
That doctor said he was stable.
and then his eyes started fluttering.

226
00:12:32.043 --> 00:12:35.046
It's not normal. I know it's not normal.
Look at his eyes.

227
00:12:35.129 --> 00:12:36.798
Okay. let's keep the gun on me.

228
00:12:37.423 --> 00:12:39.884
I'm the one you need
to worry about. right? GBI.

229
00:12:39.968 --> 00:12:43.012
So we ran a CT scan
and checked for internal bleeding.

230
00:12:43.096 --> 00:12:44.514
Both came back negative.

231
00:12:44.597 --> 00:12:46.391
And we sedated him.

232
00:12:46.474 --> 00:12:49.519
- Does Kevin have a history of seizures?
- Yes. it happened when he was a kid.

233
00:12:49.602 --> 00:12:52.146
- "Status" something.
- Mom's right. Status epilepticus.

234
00:12:52.230 --> 00:12:54.732
I can stop it with medication.
but I need my resident. okay?

235
00:12:55.525 --> 00:12:57.986
Dr. Rosen?

236
00:12:58.569 --> 00:13:00.822
Give me a loading dose of Keppra
and two of lorazepam.

237
00:13:01.406 --> 00:13:02.740
- It's down the hall.
- Mm-hmm.

238
00:13:02.824 --> 00:13:05.076
- Is that okay?
- You have one minute.

239
00:13:05.702 --> 00:13:08.288
And can someone shut that woman up?

240
00:13:08.538 --> 00:13:12.333
Okay. Nakia. you have a doctor
who's listening to you.

241
00:13:12.417 --> 00:13:15.044
He has a plan to stop the seizures.
You were right.

242
00:13:15.128 --> 00:13:16.879
There's no need for the gun anymore.
is there?

243
00:13:20.008 --> 00:13:21.843
You're okay.

244
00:13:22.969 --> 00:13:26.848
Woman. if you don't shut
your damn mouth! Shut up!

245
00:13:27.473 --> 00:13:29.684
Watch it. GBI. Back up.

246
00:13:30.268 --> 00:13:33.021
The only reason
why you listen to me is this.

247
00:13:33.104 --> 00:13:36.065
and I'm not gonna let it go
until I know that Kevin is okay.

248
00:13:36.149 --> 00:13:37.358
That's where we are.

249
00:13:37.442 --> 00:13:40.570
- Okay.
- We're out of lorazepam.

250
00:13:40.653 --> 00:13:43.156
and I can't get into the pharmacy
because we're code silver.

251
00:13:43.239 --> 00:13:44.449
I don't know what to do.

252
00:13:44.532 --> 00:13:47.368
What do you mean you're out?
Find something else. Help him.

253
00:13:47.452 --> 00:13:49.412
Seth. where else could it be?

254
00:13:49.495 --> 00:13:51.039
An ambulance would have it.

255
00:13:51.664 --> 00:13:52.957
Okay. there you go.

256
00:13:53.708 --> 00:13:55.126
SWAT's gonna be outside.

257
00:13:55.209 --> 00:13:58.296
They can deliver it.
All we need to do is ask.

258
00:13:58.379 --> 00:14:00.673
SWAT? You're lying.

259
00:14:00.757 --> 00:14:02.925
Nakia. look at me.

260
00:14:03.760 --> 00:14:05.344
You have hostages.

261
00:14:05.428 --> 00:14:07.805
That means SWAT's here. It's protocol.

262
00:14:07.889 --> 00:14:10.516
Everyone wants Kevin to be okay.

263
00:14:11.601 --> 00:14:14.103
I know exactly how this goes.

264
00:14:14.937 --> 00:14:17.065
They've already cut the phone lines.

265
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:35.416
Hey. what's the status?

266
00:14:36.125 --> 00:14:38.586
Phone lines are cut.
evac is almost complete.

267
00:14:38.669 --> 00:14:40.213
and exits have been secured.

268
00:14:40.296 --> 00:14:42.507
Okay. good. Let's keep digging
on that patient manifest

269
00:14:42.590 --> 00:14:44.175
and get Nakia Cane a sat phone.

270
00:14:44.258 --> 00:14:45.426
I'd like to say hello.

271
00:14:45.510 --> 00:14:46.511
Yes. ma'am.

272
00:14:46.594 --> 00:14:47.845
Phone.

273
00:14:52.975 --> 00:14:54.102
I got this.

274
00:14:55.561 --> 00:14:57.230
Shh...

275
00:15:00.900 --> 00:15:03.611
What is that?

276
00:15:04.612 --> 00:15:05.738
That's your sat phone.

277
00:15:06.823 --> 00:15:08.074
It's gonna ring in a second.

278
00:15:11.536 --> 00:15:13.830
Nakia. you have a very small window

279
00:15:13.913 --> 00:15:15.623
when the people outside
are willing to help.

280
00:15:16.124 --> 00:15:19.877
After that. they're gonna cut the power.
and Kevin needs these machines to work.

281
00:15:20.795 --> 00:15:24.298
Dr. McDale. how long until Doc's injury
turns into a murder charge?

282
00:15:24.841 --> 00:15:25.883
Not long.

283
00:15:25.967 --> 00:15:29.387
Kevin needs lorazepam.
Doc needs saving. You have the gun.

284
00:15:31.430 --> 00:15:32.932
I'm gonna answer the phone.

285
00:15:45.611 --> 00:15:47.572
- Trent.
- I told you to go to urgent care.

286
00:15:47.655 --> 00:15:48.656
How's it going in there?

287
00:15:48.739 --> 00:15:51.075
She needs IV lorazepam for her son.

288
00:15:51.159 --> 00:15:53.494
<i>- Is she gonna use that gun again?</i>
- If she has to.

289
00:15:53.995 --> 00:15:56.455
You've got four kids inside with you.
is that right?

290
00:15:56.539 --> 00:15:57.707
Six.

291
00:15:57.790 --> 00:15:59.333
Let me talk to her.

292
00:15:59.417 --> 00:16:02.295
Will. she hit his femoral.
Tell Seth we need blood.

293
00:16:02.378 --> 00:16:03.713
Is that Angie?

294
00:16:05.381 --> 00:16:06.841
Yep. it's a party.

295
00:16:08.301 --> 00:16:11.846
Nakia Cane. this is my partner.
Special Agent Faith Mitchell.

296
00:16:12.471 --> 00:16:13.931
How's it going in there. Nakia?

297
00:16:15.224 --> 00:16:17.476
<i>I understand
that your son needs lorazepam.</i>

298
00:16:18.311 --> 00:16:20.813
You've got six kids in that waiting room.

299
00:16:21.522 --> 00:16:23.024
How about we make a trade?

300
00:16:30.907 --> 00:16:33.784
Come on. Nakia. Everyone wins here.

301
00:16:39.665 --> 00:16:41.792
Make it fast and don't do anything stupid.

302
00:16:45.796 --> 00:16:49.926
- I need IV lorazepam. now.
- Sergeant. Go check with...

303
00:16:51.761 --> 00:16:53.054
All right.

304
00:16:54.597 --> 00:16:56.140
Snug as a bug in a rug.

305
00:16:57.683 --> 00:16:58.768
Ready to go?

306
00:16:59.769 --> 00:17:01.687
All right. Oh.

307
00:17:02.897 --> 00:17:06.192
Is this your sloth?
Can't leave without your sloth.

308
00:17:06.275 --> 00:17:07.485
His name is Leon.

309
00:17:07.568 --> 00:17:08.653
Ah.

310
00:17:09.403 --> 00:17:12.073
Of course it is. Hello. Leon.

311
00:17:12.156 --> 00:17:15.618
I know sloths like you
are very. very good at hanging on.

312
00:17:15.701 --> 00:17:18.579
I'm gonna need the two of you
to hang on tight to each other. okay?

313
00:17:19.538 --> 00:17:20.581
Here you go.

314
00:17:22.375 --> 00:17:24.168
All right.
I'm gonna follow your lead. okay?

315
00:17:24.252 --> 00:17:25.878
All right. Here we go.

316
00:17:26.379 --> 00:17:27.463
Come on.

317
00:17:36.138 --> 00:17:37.139
Hey.

318
00:17:38.057 --> 00:17:39.350
What is that. a cannon?

319
00:17:39.934 --> 00:17:40.935
No.

320
00:17:41.978 --> 00:17:43.437
It's an antique swivel gun.

321
00:17:44.063 --> 00:17:47.483
It hasn't been fired in 200 years.
and it's not very accurate.

322
00:17:47.567 --> 00:17:49.652
but someone has to do something.

323
00:17:49.735 --> 00:17:52.113
And we won the siege of Fort Ticonderoga.

324
00:17:52.196 --> 00:17:55.199
That was pretend.
Someone is doing something.

325
00:17:55.283 --> 00:17:58.703
Put that away right now. I'm a cop.

326
00:18:00.121 --> 00:18:03.958
Nico. this is Marshall and his sloth Leon.

327
00:18:04.041 --> 00:18:05.668
- What's up. Marshall?
- Hi.

328
00:18:05.751 --> 00:18:07.795
Did you know sloths only poop
one time a week?

329
00:18:07.878 --> 00:18:10.965
Lorazepam first. and then the kids.

330
00:18:11.048 --> 00:18:12.341
That's the plan.

331
00:18:12.425 --> 00:18:15.928
If anybody tries to run. I'll shoot.
Is that clear?

332
00:18:19.140 --> 00:18:20.141
Yeah.

333
00:18:24.687 --> 00:18:27.189
All right. Everybody's doing really great.

334
00:18:27.273 --> 00:18:28.566
We're gonna get you out of here.

335
00:18:31.694 --> 00:18:33.821
I should get this on board.
Every second matters.

336
00:18:36.198 --> 00:18:37.491
Okay. now the kids.

337
00:18:38.743 --> 00:18:41.746
Okay. here we go. Let's go.
Let's go. Come on.

338
00:18:42.413 --> 00:18:44.790
Come on. yeah. Here we go. Good job.

339
00:18:44.874 --> 00:18:46.334
To your right. Yep. there you go.

340
00:18:46.417 --> 00:18:48.711
McDale. you got everything
you need from outside?

341
00:18:48.794 --> 00:18:50.796
- Yeah. this should do it.
- Good.

342
00:18:54.258 --> 00:18:55.593
- Come on.
- Okay. Take it easy.

343
00:18:55.676 --> 00:18:58.137
Don't try anything
or he's not coming back.

344
00:19:12.735 --> 00:19:14.737
Lady knows how to make a point.

345
00:19:15.988 --> 00:19:17.990
Okay. okay. okay. All right. all right.

346
00:19:26.332 --> 00:19:28.209
Explain again why I can't keep this?

347
00:19:28.292 --> 00:19:30.086
It's evidence. There's blood on it.

348
00:19:30.169 --> 00:19:32.797
- Evidence that you're mean?
- Just help me turn it on.

349
00:19:34.298 --> 00:19:35.591
Yeah.

350
00:19:35.675 --> 00:19:37.885
I'm on hold. Osiris is an alias.

351
00:19:37.968 --> 00:19:40.262
No leads on his real name yet.
but I got a CI who's got his number.

352
00:19:40.346 --> 00:19:41.347
I'm trying to trace it.

353
00:19:41.430 --> 00:19:44.392
I can't believe y'all drink tap water.
Can I have this?

354
00:19:44.475 --> 00:19:45.893
That's Faith's. Put it back.

355
00:19:45.976 --> 00:19:47.978
She would want me to have it.

356
00:19:48.062 --> 00:19:49.438
Hello. What you got?

357
00:19:51.941 --> 00:19:53.275
It works.

358
00:19:53.359 --> 00:19:56.362
Oh. great. How do we find out
who owns this machine?

359
00:19:56.445 --> 00:19:59.115
It's not a machine. It's a system.

360
00:19:59.198 --> 00:20:01.117
Fifty bucks. you answer the question.

361
00:20:01.200 --> 00:20:02.451
Easy. It's right there.

362
00:20:03.035 --> 00:20:05.871
"KevCan3!"

363
00:20:05.955 --> 00:20:07.248
And his email's underneath it.

364
00:20:07.331 --> 00:20:08.833
Twenty bucks. That was too easy.

365
00:20:08.916 --> 00:20:10.084
Fifty dollars. old man.

366
00:20:10.167 --> 00:20:14.171
KevCan3@midtownersmail.com

367
00:20:15.506 --> 00:20:16.757
- Hey. Franklin.
- Yeah.

368
00:20:16.841 --> 00:20:19.427
- I got something.
- Please tell me it's Osiris's real name.

369
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:22.596
No. but this machine belongs
to Kevin Cane.

370
00:20:24.974 --> 00:20:26.976
Isn't that the name of the kid
in the hostage situation?

371
00:20:27.059 --> 00:20:30.354
- Right. That is not good.
- Why? We found our second victim.

372
00:20:30.438 --> 00:20:32.481
I still have no idea
what Osiris's real name is

373
00:20:32.565 --> 00:20:33.816
or what he looks like.

374
00:20:33.899 --> 00:20:36.610
but guess where his cell phone pinged
an hour ago and it's still there?

375
00:20:36.694 --> 00:20:38.154
Please don't say St. Peter's.

376
00:20:38.237 --> 00:20:41.741
St. Peter's. We got to tell Faith
before Osiris kills Kevin.

377
00:20:42.324 --> 00:20:43.325
Max. go to bed.

378
00:20:52.626 --> 00:20:56.130
So Osiris must have got trapped in there
when Nakia locked the place down.

379
00:20:56.213 --> 00:20:59.425
Looking to make a name for himself.
and now he's caged in surrounded by cops.

380
00:20:59.508 --> 00:21:02.011
Great. This just got twice as dangerous.

381
00:21:02.094 --> 00:21:03.471
We need to tell Will.

382
00:21:03.554 --> 00:21:04.680
What about a sat phone?

383
00:21:04.764 --> 00:21:06.807
She's not much of a phone girl.

384
00:21:07.391 --> 00:21:09.518
Okay. Pizza party?

385
00:21:11.479 --> 00:21:12.855
I know Angie's order.

386
00:21:19.403 --> 00:21:22.239
All right. it's gonna take a little while
before we see the results.

387
00:21:22.740 --> 00:21:25.326
- That's it?
- To stop his seizures. yes.

388
00:21:25.951 --> 00:21:27.703
Dr. Rosen and I would like
to use that time

389
00:21:27.787 --> 00:21:29.079
to check on the other patients.

390
00:21:29.163 --> 00:21:30.664
Everyone in that room needs help too.

391
00:21:30.748 --> 00:21:33.083
It's all happening. Nakia.
the way you wanted.

392
00:21:33.709 --> 00:21:36.253
How about we get these people
off the floor and looked at. huh?

393
00:21:36.337 --> 00:21:39.256
Stay where I can see you.

394
00:21:39.340 --> 00:21:41.175
Thank you. Thank you.

395
00:21:49.809 --> 00:21:50.810
So. um...

396
00:21:53.020 --> 00:21:55.147
what's gonna happen after this?

397
00:21:55.940 --> 00:21:59.401
I mean. I shot someone. I'm going to jail.

398
00:22:01.904 --> 00:22:03.364
I didn't want any of this.

399
00:22:04.114 --> 00:22:05.115
It's just...

400
00:22:05.950 --> 00:22:07.201
They wouldn't hear me.

401
00:22:07.284 --> 00:22:08.536
I know.

402
00:22:11.914 --> 00:22:12.957
Where'd you serve?

403
00:22:14.917 --> 00:22:15.918
I see the way you move.

404
00:22:16.001 --> 00:22:17.795
You're awfully comfortable
with that sidearm.

405
00:22:17.878 --> 00:22:19.129
You barely put your back to me.

406
00:22:20.464 --> 00:22:22.842
So where'd you serve?

407
00:22:23.592 --> 00:22:24.593
Kuwait.

408
00:22:25.719 --> 00:22:27.304
With the push in Iraq.

409
00:22:27.388 --> 00:22:29.974
Went to jump school. had a bad jump.

410
00:22:30.057 --> 00:22:31.350
Then painkillers.

411
00:22:33.561 --> 00:22:34.812
Then other stuff.

412
00:22:35.437 --> 00:22:37.022
I'm sorry it went that way for you.

413
00:22:41.986 --> 00:22:43.153
He's a good kid.

414
00:22:51.996 --> 00:22:53.539
Wants to be an engineer.

415
00:22:55.457 --> 00:22:56.834
Deserves a better mother.

416
00:22:57.543 --> 00:23:01.213
I don't know many parents
who would hold an emergency room hostage.

417
00:23:03.591 --> 00:23:06.635
It's all my fault.
I've gotten real bad lately.

418
00:23:07.511 --> 00:23:10.681
I've had to start selling things.

419
00:23:11.724 --> 00:23:13.058
Our things.

420
00:23:13.684 --> 00:23:17.187
You know. when I sold all his video games.
he wasn't even mad.

421
00:23:17.688 --> 00:23:19.356
He said he understood.

422
00:23:21.609 --> 00:23:23.068
That broke my heart.

423
00:23:24.111 --> 00:23:25.613
Did he go back to get it?

424
00:23:28.198 --> 00:23:29.366
Is that what happened?

425
00:23:31.160 --> 00:23:34.788
I know exactly what it feels like
to be the reason...

426
00:23:35.623 --> 00:23:37.583
your loved ones end up in harm's way.

427
00:23:40.085 --> 00:23:42.671
Shame. Guilt.

428
00:23:44.340 --> 00:23:45.341
Anger.

429
00:23:50.679 --> 00:23:51.680
It's terrible.

430
00:23:53.682 --> 00:23:55.309
I don't care what happens to me

431
00:23:55.935 --> 00:23:57.394
as long as he pulls through.

432
00:23:57.895 --> 00:23:59.021
Kevin will wake up.

433
00:23:59.104 --> 00:24:01.982
And when he does.
I'll make sure he stays safe.

434
00:24:03.275 --> 00:24:05.694
That's what happens when this is all over.

435
00:24:08.989 --> 00:24:09.990
What now?

436
00:24:10.074 --> 00:24:11.909
That would be the food.

437
00:24:15.746 --> 00:24:18.082
I got plain. He's got mushroom.

438
00:24:18.165 --> 00:24:19.166
Here you go.

439
00:24:19.708 --> 00:24:21.669
Hey. honey. How's desk duty?

440
00:24:21.752 --> 00:24:25.714
Oh. So good. So relaxing. Um...

441
00:24:25.798 --> 00:24:28.384
Really couldn't be better. honestly.
And how was your day?

442
00:24:28.968 --> 00:24:32.054
Uh. you know. just soaking up
this quality time before the baby comes.

443
00:24:32.596 --> 00:24:34.223
- Calm before the storm.
- Mm-hmm.

444
00:24:34.848 --> 00:24:36.433
You and Will gonna save the day?

445
00:24:37.351 --> 00:24:38.477
I think we might.

446
00:24:39.561 --> 00:24:43.524
Who wants pepperoni?
And we got "pickle and pineapple"?

447
00:24:43.607 --> 00:24:46.860
That's me. That's for me.
That's for me. That's for me.

448
00:24:46.944 --> 00:24:48.195
Okay. okay. Thank you.

449
00:24:48.278 --> 00:24:50.990
Do you have matches.
or a lighter. or something?

450
00:24:51.073 --> 00:24:52.700
Knock it off.

451
00:24:52.783 --> 00:24:55.411
Pineapples on pizza? That's disgusting.

452
00:24:55.494 --> 00:24:58.080
Yeah. a disgusting Trojan horse.

453
00:25:19.518 --> 00:25:20.811
Mind if I get something to eat?

454
00:25:22.354 --> 00:25:25.024
I'm just going right over there.
You can watch me the whole time.

455
00:25:35.117 --> 00:25:36.994
Kevin's shooter is here.

456
00:25:38.704 --> 00:25:41.498
No description. just a name. Osiris.

457
00:25:42.541 --> 00:25:43.834
Anyone make sense?

458
00:25:46.795 --> 00:25:48.839
Well. this got exponentially worse.

459
00:25:48.922 --> 00:25:50.215
- Come with me.
- Hey.

460
00:25:50.299 --> 00:25:51.675
Yeah.

461
00:25:51.759 --> 00:25:55.137
Your patient just became my crime scene.
Let's see what we can find out.

462
00:26:00.893 --> 00:26:02.061
That looks pretty fresh to me.

463
00:26:02.144 --> 00:26:04.521
Yeah. it could have happened
when he fell or in a struggle.

464
00:26:05.397 --> 00:26:07.775
Why are you guys looking at him?
What's going on?

465
00:26:08.358 --> 00:26:10.527
Nakia. there's something
I need to tell you. all right?

466
00:26:10.611 --> 00:26:13.280
And what happens next depends
on your ability to stay calm.

467
00:26:13.363 --> 00:26:15.157
Focus on Kevin. like us.

468
00:26:17.659 --> 00:26:18.660
Good.

469
00:26:20.579 --> 00:26:22.748
Who'd you sell Kevin's gaming system to?

470
00:26:23.373 --> 00:26:25.709
Why? Why are you asking now?

471
00:26:27.544 --> 00:26:31.381
I want you to look at that room.
tell me if you see anyone familiar.

472
00:26:31.465 --> 00:26:34.176
Can you do that for me? Nice and casual.

473
00:26:43.185 --> 00:26:45.813
I don't know any of these people.
Why are you asking?

474
00:26:45.896 --> 00:26:47.439
Hey. Will. check this out.

475
00:26:48.482 --> 00:26:50.109
That's skin under the nails.

476
00:26:50.192 --> 00:26:52.361
We're looking for someone
with scratch marks.

477
00:26:53.278 --> 00:26:56.323
Somebody better start telling me
what the hell is going on.

478
00:26:56.406 --> 00:26:58.117
Nice and easy. all right?

479
00:26:59.201 --> 00:27:04.832
We have reason to believe that the person
who did this to your son is here.

480
00:27:05.833 --> 00:27:08.418
Hey. hey. Nakia.
we're staying calm. remember?

481
00:27:08.502 --> 00:27:09.711
Come on. come on back.

482
00:27:12.339 --> 00:27:16.051
I'm right here with you. okay?
Now come on. Nakia. point the gun at me.

483
00:27:16.135 --> 00:27:19.012
I can keep Kevin safe. but I'm gonna
need you to let me do my job.

484
00:27:22.975 --> 00:27:25.936
Kevin?

485
00:27:26.019 --> 00:27:27.604
- What's going on?
- Rosen.

486
00:27:27.688 --> 00:27:29.147
- What do you need?
- Secure his tube now.

487
00:27:29.231 --> 00:27:31.024
bolus 50 fent. start a propofol drip.

488
00:27:31.108 --> 00:27:32.818
Grab restraints. hold his arms down.

489
00:27:32.901 --> 00:27:34.903
Kevin. Kevin. there's a tube
down your throat.

490
00:27:34.987 --> 00:27:37.948
I need you to stay still so I can give you
medicine that's gonna relax you. okay?

491
00:27:38.031 --> 00:27:40.659
- It's okay. You're okay. I'm right here.
- His BP is tanking.

492
00:27:40.742 --> 00:27:43.662
- Yeah.
- What's going on? Kevin!

493
00:27:45.747 --> 00:27:48.667
He's losing consciousness again.
Did we push the prop?

494
00:27:48.750 --> 00:27:50.627
Bottom out his pressure?
Did his tube shift?

495
00:27:50.711 --> 00:27:53.380
- No. I haven't touched his sedation.
- All right.

496
00:27:53.463 --> 00:27:54.840
Breathing sounds are good.

497
00:27:57.217 --> 00:27:58.594
He's not seizing anymore.

498
00:27:59.177 --> 00:28:00.846
You said you could save him.

499
00:28:00.929 --> 00:28:03.223
You need to let them do their job.
They know what they're doing.

500
00:28:03.307 --> 00:28:04.725
All right. hold C-spine.

501
00:28:08.228 --> 00:28:10.355
- Whoa. Heavy hemorrhaging from the GSW.
- Oh. my God.

502
00:28:10.439 --> 00:28:12.649
A fragment must have shifted
when he was grabbing for his tube.

503
00:28:12.733 --> 00:28:14.985
- Should I pack it?
- Yes. pack him now. please.

504
00:28:15.068 --> 00:28:17.446
- We gotta move him to the OR.
- Why can't you do it here?

505
00:28:17.529 --> 00:28:19.656
He needs a vascular surgeon.
That is not me.

506
00:28:19.740 --> 00:28:21.617
- You do not want me to do this here.
- God...

507
00:28:27.164 --> 00:28:29.833
- Was that a damn explosion?
- SWAT. let's go.

508
00:28:32.419 --> 00:28:33.670
You idiots.

509
00:28:39.301 --> 00:28:42.095
No! No.

510
00:28:45.682 --> 00:28:47.601
Remember.
there are innocent civilians in there.

511
00:28:47.684 --> 00:28:50.270
Hey. Faith. when this is all over.
I have something important to tell you.

512
00:28:50.354 --> 00:28:53.148
- What? What? Hey. No. don't do that.
- Too late.

513
00:28:55.150 --> 00:28:57.611
Don't let anything happen to him.
He's all I got.

514
00:28:57.694 --> 00:28:59.571
Please don't leave him alone. He needs me.

515
00:28:59.655 --> 00:29:02.449
Listen to me. You have my word.
I'll keep your son safe.

516
00:29:03.241 --> 00:29:05.410
- Seth. what can I do?
- Uh. I need blood.

517
00:29:05.494 --> 00:29:07.412
- Okay. where?
- Down the hall in the cooler.

518
00:29:07.996 --> 00:29:10.540
Rosen. how's that packing? We gotta move.
Where is the orderly?

519
00:29:10.624 --> 00:29:13.085
I'm working on it.
We need respiratory therapy.

520
00:29:13.168 --> 00:29:15.587
They all evacuated. This kid's got minutes
until he bleeds out.

521
00:29:15.671 --> 00:29:17.506
- Here's your blood.
- Thank you.

522
00:29:18.590 --> 00:29:19.800
- Doc.
- Great.

523
00:29:19.883 --> 00:29:22.386
I need you at the end of the gurney
with Will. You guys get ready to steer.

524
00:29:22.469 --> 00:29:23.720
Rosen. what is the holdup?

525
00:29:23.804 --> 00:29:27.099
- He's packed. he has O2. go.
- Go. To the elevator. please. Let's go.

526
00:29:27.724 --> 00:29:30.102
- Thank you.
- Make a hole here. Get out of the way.

527
00:29:30.686 --> 00:29:34.022
Make a hole. Clear out this path.
Let's go. thank you so much.

528
00:29:34.106 --> 00:29:37.401
Thank you. make space. Take care of her.
please. Make space here. let's go.

529
00:29:37.484 --> 00:29:39.486
Everyone freeze!
Put your hands where I can see them!

530
00:29:39.569 --> 00:29:42.614
Hey. hey. hey! I'm GBI.
We need to move this kid. He's gonna die.

531
00:29:42.698 --> 00:29:44.700
- Get on the floor!
- Stand down. Baker. Let him through.

532
00:29:44.783 --> 00:29:46.326
- Move. move!
- We gotta get to the OR!

533
00:29:46.410 --> 00:29:48.745
- Polaski. you good?
- I'm good. Get somebody to secure

534
00:29:48.829 --> 00:29:50.664
- that stupid cannon.
- Back up.

535
00:29:59.214 --> 00:30:01.425
- We were trying to help. We're war heroes.
- Let's go. Now.

536
00:30:01.508 --> 00:30:03.343
- Somebody should help that guy.
- Get a gurney.

537
00:30:03.427 --> 00:30:05.804
I need everybody
to stay exactly where they are!

538
00:30:05.887 --> 00:30:08.223
- Where's Nakia Cane?
- With security. unarmed.

539
00:30:08.807 --> 00:30:09.850
Baker. come with me.

540
00:30:10.642 --> 00:30:13.061
Help me!

541
00:30:13.145 --> 00:30:15.188
Okay. yeah. let's bring it down.
Okay. let's calm down.

542
00:30:15.272 --> 00:30:17.315
All right. bring it down.
These are the good guys.

543
00:30:21.445 --> 00:30:24.322
Take it easy. right? Okay.

544
00:30:24.406 --> 00:30:26.283
Hey. Polaski! Get over here.

545
00:30:32.039 --> 00:30:34.583
- Come on. people. Go. go. go.
- What happened?

546
00:30:35.876 --> 00:30:37.502
Well. it wasn't a cannonball.

547
00:30:39.796 --> 00:30:42.299
She's a nurse.
She must have walked in on something?

548
00:30:49.556 --> 00:30:50.891
A pair of scrubs is missing.

549
00:30:53.810 --> 00:30:56.271
You know. there's an orderly
who's been in there all day.

550
00:30:56.897 --> 00:30:58.065
I don't see his picture here.

551
00:30:58.148 --> 00:31:00.567
Talking about the guy who got
in the elevator with Will and Seth?

552
00:31:01.902 --> 00:31:02.903
Go.

553
00:31:04.654 --> 00:31:08.408
- Here we go.
- This way. Let's go. Let's move.

554
00:31:09.034 --> 00:31:10.035
All right.

555
00:31:11.411 --> 00:31:13.663
- Come on. Kevin. Stay with me.
- Take us to ten.

556
00:31:37.938 --> 00:31:39.523
Osiris. right?

557
00:31:40.190 --> 00:31:43.527
I know this isn't how you saw
your day going. Me neither.

558
00:31:44.069 --> 00:31:46.279
But I made a promise
to keep this kid alive.

559
00:31:46.363 --> 00:31:49.199
So. how about you and me get off
on the next floor and work it out?

560
00:31:52.577 --> 00:31:54.371
How about I finish what I started?

561
00:32:05.006 --> 00:32:06.174
- Thank you.
- Yep.

562
00:32:40.125 --> 00:32:42.502
- Nice timing.
- Osiris?

563
00:32:42.586 --> 00:32:43.587
Oh. yeah.

564
00:32:46.047 --> 00:32:47.090
Come on.

565
00:33:15.243 --> 00:33:17.412
He cut the bag. I don't have any pressure.

566
00:33:25.670 --> 00:33:26.838
Son of a...

567
00:33:27.756 --> 00:33:29.007
No!

568
00:33:29.758 --> 00:33:32.802
GBI! Call up to eight.
have someone call the elevator.

569
00:33:49.194 --> 00:33:50.362
Still going?

570
00:33:50.445 --> 00:33:51.821
What. you stop for a pee break?

571
00:34:09.506 --> 00:34:10.757
All right. this is me.

572
00:34:13.260 --> 00:34:15.428
- You good?
- Yeah. I got it from here.

573
00:34:17.222 --> 00:34:18.598
No. stay down.

574
00:34:18.682 --> 00:34:22.310
You're under arrest
for the attempted murder of Kevin Cane.

575
00:34:22.394 --> 00:34:25.981
As well as actual murder.
drug trafficking.

576
00:34:27.482 --> 00:34:28.608
and being an a-hole.

577
00:34:33.655 --> 00:34:35.240
Press the button. Ormewood.

578
00:34:35.323 --> 00:34:37.993
You "press the button. Ormewood."

579
00:34:38.076 --> 00:34:39.202
I'm too tired.

580
00:34:40.996 --> 00:34:42.163
Okay. fine.

581
00:34:45.375 --> 00:34:46.459
I can't.

582
00:34:47.127 --> 00:34:48.795
Just press the damn button. you're closer.

583
00:34:48.878 --> 00:34:51.172
You flipped over me. That was so cool.

584
00:34:52.048 --> 00:34:54.259
It was pretty cool.

585
00:34:54.884 --> 00:34:58.305
Okay. I'll do it. I'll do it. Here we go.

586
00:34:59.889 --> 00:35:01.808
Nice shot.

587
00:35:02.309 --> 00:35:03.393
Okay.

588
00:35:09.024 --> 00:35:10.525
- Thanks.
- Of course.

589
00:35:11.234 --> 00:35:14.112
Hey. I heard you kicked some ass in there.

590
00:35:15.488 --> 00:35:18.700
- How you holding up?
- Well. first cancer. now this.

591
00:35:18.783 --> 00:35:20.910
I hate hospitals.

592
00:35:22.037 --> 00:35:26.541
Well. I hope that you never
have to go in one for a very long time.

593
00:35:26.625 --> 00:35:27.626
Yeah.

594
00:35:28.627 --> 00:35:29.628
All right.

595
00:35:33.214 --> 00:35:34.215
Thanks. Mitchell.

596
00:35:36.468 --> 00:35:39.721
Greedy-ass hostages ate all the pizza.

597
00:35:39.804 --> 00:35:42.432
- I'm buying dinner. Come on.
- Oh. look at us. best friends.

598
00:35:42.515 --> 00:35:44.976
Hey. what was that
that you wanted to tell me earlier?

599
00:35:46.728 --> 00:35:48.605
Franklin drank
your last Super Orange Drank.

600
00:35:48.688 --> 00:35:50.857
- Wow.
- Seriously?

601
00:35:51.441 --> 00:35:55.028
Uh. I'm sorry. Super sorry.
I-I'll replace it.

602
00:35:55.111 --> 00:35:57.781
Okay. so what about my trust?
Are you gonna replace that?

603
00:35:58.406 --> 00:36:00.617
Hey. we're gonna get dinner.
You wanna join?

604
00:36:00.700 --> 00:36:02.786
Next time. I have plans.

605
00:36:03.328 --> 00:36:04.496
See you at work. partner.

606
00:36:05.872 --> 00:36:07.123
You're driving.

607
00:36:17.175 --> 00:36:18.927
I just talked to Dr. McDale.

608
00:36:20.136 --> 00:36:21.346
Kevin's gonna be okay.

609
00:36:30.271 --> 00:36:31.940
I did what I had to do.

610
00:36:32.941 --> 00:36:34.192
He's my baby.

611
00:36:35.694 --> 00:36:36.695
I know.

612
00:36:54.003 --> 00:36:56.840
Is it hot in here or is it just me?

613
00:36:56.923 --> 00:36:59.843
Uh...
I think that's the pregnant.

614
00:36:59.926 --> 00:37:02.429
Right? Oh. God.

615
00:37:02.512 --> 00:37:04.472
- Does it hurt?
- No.

616
00:37:04.556 --> 00:37:05.557
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

617
00:37:05.640 --> 00:37:08.810
It does. but just when I do... anything.

618
00:37:08.893 --> 00:37:10.645
Then don't do anything.

619
00:37:11.271 --> 00:37:12.605
Don't.

620
00:37:12.689 --> 00:37:14.566
- Hey.
- Hi.

621
00:37:19.946 --> 00:37:21.197
Today was...

622
00:37:22.615 --> 00:37:24.701
It was really scary. babe.

623
00:37:24.784 --> 00:37:25.910
Yeah. I know.

624
00:37:28.288 --> 00:37:29.789
You were amazing.

625
00:37:31.875 --> 00:37:33.209
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

626
00:37:36.796 --> 00:37:37.797
I guess...

627
00:37:40.216 --> 00:37:41.509
Is that what it's like for you?

628
00:37:42.594 --> 00:37:44.304
Waiting for me to come home from work?

629
00:37:44.846 --> 00:37:46.014
I'm okay.

630
00:37:47.307 --> 00:37:48.308
We're okay.

631
00:37:49.601 --> 00:37:50.602
Yeah.

632
00:37:56.649 --> 00:37:58.234
- Thanks for that.
- Mmm.

633
00:38:13.124 --> 00:38:14.751
Where's the mandoline?

634
00:38:15.794 --> 00:38:17.170
I threw it out.

635
00:38:17.253 --> 00:38:19.672
What? Why? You love scalloped potatoes.

636
00:38:19.756 --> 00:38:21.132
I don't care.

637
00:38:22.175 --> 00:38:25.011
I can't let anyone else I love get hurt.

638
00:38:27.472 --> 00:38:28.890
Did you just say you loved me?

639
00:38:31.351 --> 00:38:33.394
Will. my God.

640
00:38:33.478 --> 00:38:34.938
I'm gonna faint again.

641
00:38:35.021 --> 00:38:37.440
What? I don't know what
you're talking about. I didn't say that.

642
00:38:37.524 --> 00:38:39.192
Betty. did you hear me say that. girl?

643
00:38:39.275 --> 00:38:40.401
Ah! That's a yes bark.

644
00:38:40.485 --> 00:38:43.947
That was absolutely
a "I need to go on a walk" bark. so...

645
00:38:44.030 --> 00:38:47.408
She just confirmed. Go ahead.

646
00:38:50.411 --> 00:38:52.539
Okay. okay. I'll get the leash.

647
00:39:29.993 --> 00:39:30.994
Adelaide.

648
00:39:32.495 --> 00:39:34.956
<i>Hello. Will. How are you?</i>

649
00:39:35.039 --> 00:39:36.165
<i>I missed you.</i>

650
00:39:36.249 --> 00:39:38.293
<i>Isn't that strange?</i>

651
00:39:38.376 --> 00:39:39.544
Where's Antonio?

652
00:39:40.837 --> 00:39:42.589
Is he alive? Put him on the phone.

653
00:39:42.672 --> 00:39:46.259
<i>Now. now. come on.
You're smarter than that.</i>

654
00:39:46.342 --> 00:39:49.304
<i>What's the question
you should be asking me?</i>

655
00:39:50.930 --> 00:39:51.931
What do you want?

656
00:39:53.182 --> 00:39:54.851
<i>All sorts of things.</i>

657
00:39:55.852 --> 00:39:58.563
<i>Do you ever think about the jungle?</i>

658
00:39:59.272 --> 00:40:02.942
<i>I gotta say. that was a lot of fun.</i>

659
00:40:08.448 --> 00:40:10.074
The only thing I think about...

660
00:40:11.910 --> 00:40:13.286
is finding you.

661
00:40:14.704 --> 00:40:15.997
And I will.

662
00:40:16.998 --> 00:40:20.418
<i>Oh! Well. you're in luck.</i>

663
00:40:20.501 --> 00:40:22.420
<i>I'm coming to you.</i>

664
00:40:23.338 --> 00:40:25.673
<i>But if you tell anyone about this call.</i>

665
00:40:25.757 --> 00:40:28.927
<i>I'll remove your uncle's organs
with a rusty spoon and a smile.</i>

666
00:40:29.469 --> 00:40:32.472
<i>so be a good boy. Special Agent Trent.</i>

667
00:40:32.555 --> 00:40:34.307
I'll be waiting.

667
